
[1]disquisition

   DISQUISITION, n. [L., to seek.] A formal or systematic inquiry into any
   subject, by arguments, or discussion of the facts and circumstances
   that may elucidate truth; as a disquistion on government or morals; a
   disquistion concerning the antediluvian earth. [It is usually applied
   to a written treatise.]
